<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Ruby on Zaft Memory Core</title><link>https://davmig.github.io/tags/ruby/</link><description>Recent content in Ruby on Zaft Memory Core</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Thu, 08 Dec 2016 22:54:49 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://davmig.github.io/tags/ruby/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>ruby学习笔记</title><link>https://davmig.github.io/posts/2016-12-08-ruby-notes/</link><pubDate>Thu, 08 Dec 2016 22:54:49 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://davmig.github.io/posts/2016-12-08-ruby-notes/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="regular-expressions">regular expressions&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>&lt;code>=~&lt;/code>是用于正则表达式的匹配操作符。返回匹配到的字符串位置或nil。&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#282a36;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;">&lt;code class="language-ruby" data-lang="ruby">&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">1&lt;/span>&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#34;abcdef&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=~&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">/d/&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"># return 3&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span style="display:flex;">&lt;span style="white-space:pre;-webkit-user-select:none;user-select:none;margin-right:0.4em;padding:0 0.4em 0 0.4em;color:#7f7f7f">2&lt;/span>&lt;span>&lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">&amp;#34;aaaaaa&amp;#34;&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#ff79c6">=~&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#f1fa8c">/d/&lt;/span> &lt;span style="color:#6272a4"># return nil&lt;/span>
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h2 id="和">!和?&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>The exclamation point (!, sometimes pronounced aloud as &amp;ldquo;bang!&amp;rdquo;) indicates something potentially destructive, that is to say, something that can change the value of what it touches.&lt;/p>
&lt;pre tabindex="0">&lt;code>ruby&amp;gt; s1 = &amp;#34;forth&amp;#34;
 &amp;#34;forth&amp;#34;
ruby&amp;gt; s1.chop! # This changes s1.
 &amp;#34;fort&amp;#34;
ruby&amp;gt; s2 = s1.chop # This puts a changed copy in s2,
 &amp;#34;for&amp;#34;
ruby&amp;gt; s1 # ... without disturbing s1.
 &amp;#34;fort&amp;#34;
&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;p>You&amp;rsquo;ll also sometimes see chomp and chomp! used. These are more selective: the end of a string gets bit off only if it happens to be a newline.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>